#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3641
#, no-wrap
msgid "Feature Auto-Activation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3645
msgid ""
"When using a GNU configure script, keep an eye on which optional features "
"are activated by auto-detection. Explicitly disable optional features that "
"are not needed by adding `--without-xxx` or `--disable-xxx` in "
"`CONFIGURE_ARGS`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3646
#, no-wrap
msgid "Wrong Handling of an Option"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3652
#, no-wrap
msgid "if ${PORT_OPTIONS:MFOO}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3655
msgid "LIB_DEPENDS+=\t\tlibfoo.so:devel/foo CONFIGURE_ARGS+=\t--enable-foo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3662
msgid ""
"In the example above, imagine a library libfoo is installed on the system. "
"The user does not want this application to use libfoo, so he toggled the "
"option off in the `make config` dialog. But the application's configure "
"script detects the library present in the system and includes its support in "
"the resulting executable. Now when the user decides to remove libfoo from "
"the system, the ports system does not protest (no dependency on libfoo was "
"recorded) but the application breaks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3663
#, no-wrap
msgid "Correct Handling of an Option"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3674
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"....\n"
"FOO_LIB_DEPENDS=\t\tlibfoo.so:devel/foo\n"
"# Will add --enable-foo / --disable-foo\n"
"FOO_CONFIGURE_ENABLE=\tfoo\n"
"....\n"
"\n"
"====\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:3680
