#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4281
msgid "Values containing whitespace must be enclosed in quotes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4290
msgid ""
"....  OPT_VARS=\tfoo=\"bar baz\" ....  This is due to the way man:make[1] "
"variable expansion deals with whitespace. When `OPT_VARS= foo=bar baz` is "
"expanded, the variable ends up containing two strings, `foo=bar` and `baz`. "
"But the submitter probably intended there to be only one string, `foo=bar "
"baz`. Quoting the value prevents whitespace from being used as a delimiter.  "
